#: src/native-libraries/overview.md:137
msgid ""
"Perry's codegen translates the user's TS-side calls "
"(`mysql.createConnection(config)`, `c.query(sql, params)`) into direct calls "
"to these symbols, with the right argument coercion (JsValue NaN-box ↔ f64 "
"ABI shim, string-pointer extraction, etc.)."
msgstr ""

#: src/native-libraries/overview.md:142
msgid "4. Linking"
msgstr ""

#: src/native-libraries/overview.md:144
msgid ""
"The staticlib (`libperry_ext_mysql2.a` for the well-known case, or a "
"prebuilt artifact in `node_modules/mysql2/prebuilt/<target>/` for the "
"external case) joins the link line alongside `libperry_runtime.a` and "
"`libperry_stdlib.a`. The `js_mysql2_*` symbol references in the user's "
"compiled code resolve at link time."
msgstr ""

#: src/native-libraries/overview.md:150
msgid ""
"If the binding ships only Rust source (no prebuilt), Perry runs `cargo build "
"--release` on the wrapper at compile time. Slow first build, then cached."
msgstr ""

#: src/native-libraries/overview.md:154
msgid "5. Runtime"
msgstr ""

#: src/native-libraries/overview.md:156
msgid ""
"User code runs. Calls into `js_mysql2_*` happen at native speed — function "
"call overhead is one register-pass for the receiver handle plus one each per "
"param. Promise resolution / closure invocation / async work bridge through "
"perry-ffi's surface (`JsPromise`, `JsClosure`, `spawn_blocking + "
"tokio::Handle::current().block_on`). The wrapper sees Perry's NaN-boxed "
"JsValues directly; user TypeScript sees a normal Promise / object / array."
msgstr ""

