#: src/cli/fast-math.md:11
msgid ""
"Yes (~94% of random FP programs match Node bit-for-bit; the residual ~6% "
"comes from the LLVM SLP vectorizer at `-O3`, not from fast-math)"
msgstr ""

#: src/cli/fast-math.md:11
msgid "Same as Node within noise on realistic FP code"
msgstr ""

#: src/cli/fast-math.md:12 src/cli/fast-math.md:86 src/cli/fast-math.md:110
msgid "`--fast-math`"
msgstr ""

#: src/cli/fast-math.md:12
msgid "No (~70%; ~30% of random FP programs diverge by 1 ULP)"
msgstr ""

#: src/cli/fast-math.md:12
msgid ""
"~7x faster on tight `sum += constant` loops; ~0% difference on dot products, "
"array reductions, or any data-dependent FP-heavy code (M-series ARM64 "
"numbers; x86_64 may differ)"
msgstr ""

#: src/cli/fast-math.md:14
msgid ""
"If your program does scientific computing, signal processing, or any "
"hand-tuned numeric kernel that benefits from autovectorization or FMA "
"fusion, `--fast-math` may help. For everything else (UI, business logic, "
"crypto, networking, framework code), it changes nothing observable except "
"correctness — leave it off."
msgstr ""

#: src/cli/fast-math.md:20
msgid "Three ways to enable it"
msgstr ""

#: src/cli/fast-math.md:22
msgid "CLI flag wins over env var, env var wins over package.json:"
msgstr ""

#: src/cli/fast-math.md:25
msgid "# 1. Per-build CLI flag\n"
msgstr ""

#: src/cli/fast-math.md:27
msgid "# 2. Per-shell environment\n"
msgstr ""

#: src/cli/fast-math.md:30
msgid "# 3. Per-project package.json (most common)\n"
msgstr ""

#: src/cli/fast-math.md:34
msgid "\"fastMath\""
msgstr ""

#: src/cli/fast-math.md:39
msgid "What it actually changes"
msgstr ""

#: src/cli/fast-math.md:41
msgid ""
"Exactly two LLVM per-instruction fast-math flags become emitted on every "
"`fadd` / `fsub` / `fmul` / `fdiv` / `frem` / `fneg`:"
msgstr ""

#: src/cli/fast-math.md:44
msgid ""
"**`reassoc`** — permits the optimizer to reorder associative chains. `(a + "
"b) + c` may become `a + (b + c)`. This is what the loop-vectorizer needs to "
"break a serial accumulator dependency chain into 4 parallel accumulators. "
"Worst-case observable behavior: tiny ULP-level differences in long sum "
"chains over operands of widely-different magnitudes; rewrites like `(a / b) "
"* b → (a * b) / b` (algebraically equal, IEEE-different)."
msgstr ""

#: src/cli/fast-math.md:52
msgid ""
"**`contract`** — permits fused multiply-add. `a * b + c` may become a single "
"FMA instruction with one rounding step instead of two. ARM and modern x86 "
"both have hardware FMA. Worst-case observable behavior: intermediate `a * b` "
"no longer rounds independently, so code that depends on the rounding "
"structure (Kahan summation, compensated arithmetic) sees different bits."
msgstr ""

#: src/cli/fast-math.md:59
msgid "What it deliberately does NOT enable"
msgstr ""

#: src/cli/fast-math.md:61
msgid ""
"The full clang `-ffast-math` is **off** even with `--fast-math`. In "
"particular, these flags stay clear:"
msgstr ""

#: src/cli/fast-math.md:64
msgid ""
"`nnan` / `ninf` — these tell LLVM to assume no NaN/Inf inputs, which is "
"catastrophic for Perry: NaN-boxing uses NaN bit patterns for every "
"non-number value (strings, objects, null, undefined, booleans). Enabling "
"them caused LLVM to replace `TAG_NULL` / `TAG_UNDEFINED` constants with "
"`0.0` at codegen time. Tried at v0.2.x commit `083ce16`, reverted two days "
"later in `b5a8c83f`. Will not return."
msgstr ""

#: src/cli/fast-math.md:70
msgid ""
"`nsz` (no signed zeros) — would make `(a + 0) → a` a valid rewrite even when "
"`a` is `-0`. `Object.is(-0, 0)` is observable in JS."
msgstr ""

#: src/cli/fast-math.md:72
msgid ""
"`arcp` (allow reciprocal) — would rewrite `a / b → a * (1 / b)`, which loses "
"precision when `b` is far from a power of two."
msgstr ""

#: src/cli/fast-math.md:74
msgid ""
"`afn` (approximate functions) — would let LLVM substitute lower- precision "
"math intrinsics."
msgstr ""

#: src/cli/fast-math.md:77
msgid ""
"For reference, Rust nightly's `#![feature(float_algebraic)]` enables "
"`reassoc + contract + nsz + arcp + afn`. Perry's `--fast-math` is strictly "
"more conservative than that."
msgstr ""

#: src/cli/fast-math.md:81
msgid "Performance numbers"
msgstr ""

#: src/cli/fast-math.md:83
msgid ""
"Benchmarks on Apple Silicon (M-series, ARM64), `min` of 3 runs each, LLVM "
"19, perry 0.5.569. Run `scripts/perf_bench.sh` to reproduce."
msgstr ""

#: src/cli/fast-math.md:86
msgid "Benchmark"
msgstr ""

#: src/cli/fast-math.md:86
msgid "Ratio"
msgstr ""

#: src/cli/fast-math.md:86
msgid "Node"
msgstr ""

#: src/cli/fast-math.md:88
msgid "`sum_loop` (100M `sum += 1`)"
msgstr ""

#: src/cli/fast-math.md:88
msgid "96 ms"
msgstr ""

#: src/cli/fast-math.md:88 src/cli/fast-math.md:89
msgid "13 ms"
msgstr ""

#: src/cli/fast-math.md:88
msgid "**7.4× faster**"
msgstr ""

#: src/cli/fast-math.md:88
msgid "53 ms"
msgstr ""

#: src/cli/fast-math.md:89
msgid "`dot_product` (10M `sum += a[i]*b[i]`)"
msgstr ""

#: src/cli/fast-math.md:89 src/cli/fast-math.md:90
msgid "1.00×"
msgstr ""

#: src/cli/fast-math.md:89
msgid "12 ms"
msgstr ""

#: src/cli/fast-math.md:90
msgid "`array_sum` (10M `sum += xs[i]`)"
msgstr ""

#: src/cli/fast-math.md:90
msgid "10 ms"
msgstr ""

#: src/cli/fast-math.md:90
msgid "11 ms"
msgstr ""

#: src/cli/fast-math.md:92
msgid ""
"Read these together: `--fast-math` produces a large speedup ONLY on loops "
"where the accumulator step is constant or trivially-redundant enough that "
"LLVM can split it into parallel partial sums. Real FP workloads rarely look "
"like `sum += 1` and so rarely benefit. The default mode beats Node on "
"`array_sum` and matches it on `dot_product` without giving up bit-exact "
"parity."
msgstr ""

#: src/cli/fast-math.md:99
msgid "Correctness numbers"
msgstr ""

#: src/cli/fast-math.md:101
msgid ""
"`scripts/fp_fuzz.mjs` — randomly generates TS programs exercising the six "
"patterns most likely to trip per-instruction FMFs (left-fold, tree-fold, "
"right-fold reductions; FMA-shaped chains; algebraic identities like "
"`(a/b)*b`; cancellation predicates). Each program is compiled with both Node "
"and Perry, and stdout is diffed byte-for-byte."
msgstr ""

#: src/cli/fast-math.md:107
msgid "Pass rate (100 random programs, seed=200)"
msgstr ""

#: src/cli/fast-math.md:109
msgid "94/100"
msgstr ""

#: src/cli/fast-math.md:110
msgid "~70/100"
msgstr ""

#: src/cli/fast-math.md:112
msgid ""
"The 6/100 default-mode failures are residual divergences from sources not "
"gated by per-instruction FMFs — most originate in the LLVM SLP vectorizer at "
"`-O3`, which can apply pairwise reduction even without the `reassoc` "
"permission. Tracked separately; out of scope for this flag."
msgstr ""

#: src/cli/fast-math.md:118
msgid "Object-cache interaction"
msgstr ""

#: src/cli/fast-math.md:120
msgid ""
"Perry's per-module `.o` cache (in `.perry-cache/objects/`) keys on the "
"`fast_math` setting alongside source hash and other compile options. "
"Toggling the flag invalidates affected cache entries — `perry --fast-math` "
"right after `perry` does a clean recompile of every module that contains f64 "
"arithmetic. No `--no-cache` necessary."
msgstr ""

#: src/cli/fast-math.md:126
msgid ""
"(This is a deliberate fix. During the original investigation, an early "
"version of the flag forgot to enter the cache key, and the result was that "
"toggling the flag appeared to do nothing because all `.o` files came from "
"the cache. If you ever see fast-math defaults that _seem_ not to take "
"effect, suspect the cache key first.)"
msgstr ""

#: src/cli/fast-math.md:132
msgid "Migration notes"
msgstr ""

#: src/cli/fast-math.md:134
msgid ""
"**For library authors:** if your TS library publishes benchmark numbers, "
"document which mode you measured under. The 7× sum-loop case is the only "
"place the gap is large; if your benchmark doesn't look like that, the "
"numbers are mode-independent and you can publish one set."
msgstr ""

#: src/cli/fast-math.md:139
msgid ""
"**For app authors:** there is no migration. Default behavior is the pre-flag "
"behavior with `--fast-math` removed; bit-exact results are _more_ compatible "
"with Node, not less."
msgstr ""

#: src/cli/fast-math.md:142
msgid ""
"**For determinism-critical code** (lockstep simulations, financial "
"reconciliation, hash function correctness): leave the default. Even with "
"`--fast-math` off there's a residual ~6% divergence rate on random FP code, "
"which is too high for true determinism work — but it's an order of magnitude "
"better than the ~30% with the flag on."
msgstr ""

#: src/cli/perry-toml.md:3
msgid ""
"`perry.toml` is the project-level configuration file for Perry. It controls "
"project metadata, build settings, platform-specific options, code signing, "
"distribution, auditing, and verification."
